Label: Break
Comment:
Break in a series of data occurring when there is a significant change in the
definitions or conditions of data collection, meaning that data before the break
cannot be directly compared with data after the break.

Label: Confidential
Comment:
Where presentation of data would disclose confidential information, for example
being able to identify details about a single respondent, this data must be
suppressed and given this marker to maintain confidentiality clauses.

Label: Earliest
Comment:
A period for which the earliest revision was made in a particular time series. No other
periods are then marked with a revision. No revisions have been made to earlier
periods.

Label: Estimated
Comment: The particular value yielded by an estimator in a given set of circumstances.

Label: Forecast
Comment:
The statistical value is forecasted. It is not an observed value; it is a calculated future
value.

Label: Rounds to zero
Comment:
For figures that round to zero, so appear as zero in a rounded table, but are not
actually zero. Note that “0” should only be used without a symbol when a figure is a
true zero.

Label: Low reliability
Comment:
This indicates observations/values for which the user should be aware of the low
quality, for example where values of statistical significance have been calculated.

Label: Not applicable
Comment: The 'z' symbol is only to be used when an observation is not applicable.

Label: Not available
Comment: For use when data is unavailable for any other reason.

Label: Not significant
Comment: The figure is not statistically significant (different definition to Eurostat standard).

Label: Provisional
Comment:
For use when the data are yet to be finalised, or are expected (or almost certainly
expected) to be revised.

Label: Revised
Comment: The figure stated has been revised since it was first published. Not to be confused with 'earliest revision'.

Label: Significant at 0.05 level
Comment:
The figure is statistically significant, and there is only a 5% probability that the result
was due to chance.

Label: Significant at 0.01 level
Comment:
The figure is statistically significant, and there is only a 1% probability that the result
was due to chance.

Label: Significant at 0.001 level
Comment:
The figure is statistically significant, and there is only a 0.1% probability that the
result was due to chance.

Label: low sample count
Comment: * numbers hidden due to very low sample count (less than 10) within this category.
